<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-08-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-08-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="23" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d23">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 7661/5.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Buenos
                                        Aires</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-08-02"><hi rend="italic">August 2,
                                1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Beaupré informs Mr. Root that the shipment of deviled ham referred
                            to in his telegram of the 19th ultimo has been again analyzed by the
                            Government, found to contain no boric acid, and passed.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>